1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Ever wonder how a tiny fish can hold toxins more than a shark?

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:10,800
This is biomagnification—when toxins increase in concentration as they move up the food chain.

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:12,400
Small organisms absorb pollutants.

4
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:16,000
Then, larger predators eat them, amplifying the toxin levels.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:22,400
Studies show that top predators can have toxin levels a thousand times higher than their prey.

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:27,200
This affects not just wildlife, but also human health through our seafood.

7
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:30,000
Stay informed about what’s on your plate.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,200
Knowledge is power!
